                <div class="columns u-margin--b-m">
                    <p>I was very pleased with the Vue app, especially how smoothly the Order Summary functioned, but the piece that stole the show for me was when we figured out the dynamic PDF generation feature. We used a webkit to PDF library to power it. I researched which version of webkit it supported, tuned Autoprefixer to handle it appropriately, and proceed to figure out a layout that would work for it. Doing this allowed us to customize the PDF to the userâ€™s purchase. This included a custom cover and information about the main attraction, as well as any additional tickets or gift cards the user purchased, all in one document that you download. This PDF was sent in an email and also available on the Order History page on the Vacation Planner site. I had never done something like this before, and I was very pleased with the final product.</p>
